data.name: Hearty Vegetable and Bean Chili
data.quickTastyDescription: A robust and flavorful chili packed with veggies and beans, perfect for a cozy meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper, carrot, and celery. Saut√© until softened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in minced garlic and cook for another minute until fragrant.
Add canned diced tomatoes, black beans, kidney beans, vegetable broth, and corn.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper.
Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce heat and let simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary. Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro if desired.
data.modifiersForBase: Add more vegetables or beans as desired.
